  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2016",
  "title": "The currentRefinedValues widget doesn't show multi level values for hierarchicalMenu refinements",
  "body": "In the current implementation of the currentRefinedValues widget, when a sub level in a hierarchicalMenu is selected, only the deeper level is available & available in the currentRefinedValues state. \r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1101220/23456207/c2783eaa-fe72-11e6-8b05-19780e295ade.png)\r\n\r\n```js\r\n{\r\n  type: \"hierarchical\",\r\n  attributeName: \"hierarchicalCategories.lvl0\",\r\n  name: \"PlayStation 4\",\r\n  count: 7,\r\n  cssClasses: Object\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWould be useful to have the full path, as it's exposed in the [JS helper via the getHierarchicalFacetBreadcrumb method](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js#asking-for-the-current-breadcrumb) ",
